<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 06 at 3:30PM CDT until June 06 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Morristown has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Marion County in east Tennessee...
* Until 400 PM CDT.
* At 329 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Tracy City,
or 12 miles northwest of Jasper, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Monteagle, Fiery Gizzard State Park and Foster Falls State Park.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
